Antonium] See the oration Pro Caelio, and the noteon c. 31 .——‘ provinciam Galliam ε ’ the consular provinces assigned to the con- suls in the year 13.c. 64 were Macedonia and Gallia Cisalpina. Dion Cassius (37, c. 33) says that Cicero had got Macedonia for his province, and that he gave it up to An- tonius, and took Gallia Cisalpina, which he afterwards declined also. Plutarch speaks in an ambiguous way, as if Cicero yielded to Antonius’ wishes at once and let him take Macedonia.
